Topic: Contact Manager

Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations
Contact Manager          The name of the website
SMS                      Short Message Service

Funtional Requirement
1. Contact
1.1 The add contact function shall allow the user to add a contact.
	1.1.1 The system shall allow the user to add a new contact.
	1.1.2 The system shall ask the user for first name, last name, a phone number, a photo when adding a new contact.
	1.1.3 The system shall allow the user to add multiple phone numbers. (no more than 5)
	1.1.4 The system may allow the user to add email, company, job title, department, and birthday when adding a new contact.

1.2 The edit contact function shall allow the user to edit a contact.
	1.2.1 The system shall allow the user to edit the first name, last name, phone number, photo.
	1.2.2 The system may allow the user to edit email, company, job title, department, and birthday.

1.3 The view contact function shall allow the user to view the contact list.
	1.3.1 The system shall allow the user to view all the contacts in alphabetical order.
	1.3.2 The system shall show the contact first name and last name.
	1.3.3 The system may show the A to Z character in alphabetical order.

1.4 The delete contact function shall allow the user to delete a contact.
	1.4.1 The system shall allow the user to delete a contact.
	1.4.2 The system shall delete the contact in a database, and the contact can’t be recovered.

1.5 The adding a photo label function shall allow the user to add a photo for a contact.
	1.5.1 The system shall allow the user to add one photo for a contact.
	1.5.2 The system shall allow the user to take a picture for the contact photo.
	1.5.3 The system shall allow the user to choose a picture from a photo library.
	1.5.4 The system may allow the user to move or scale the photo to select the part that the user wants to upload.

1.6 The search contacts function shall allow the user to search a contact by a contact name.
	1.6.1 The system shall match the searching characters with the first and last name of a contact.
	1.6.2 The system shall display the first and last name of a contact as a searching result.  
	1.6.2 The system shall display “No Results” if searching characters can’t be matched.
 
1.7 The blacklist function shall allow the user to block phones and SMS.
	1.7.1 The system shall block the SMS if the user blocks the phones. And the user will not receive any phone call and messages from people on the block list.
	1.7.2 The system may allow the user to unblock the phones.
	
1.8 The make phone calls function shall allow the user to call directly.
1.9 The send SMS function shall allow the user to send SMS directly.


2. Contact Organization
2.1 The add contact groups function shall allow users to add a group.
	2.1.1 The system shall allow a user to create a new group.
	2.1.2 The system shall ask the user for a group name and may ask user for group description and group image.
	2.1.3 The system shall allow the user to select a contact from the existing contacts.
	2.1.4 The system shall allow the user to select a contact by searching contact name. 
	
2.2 The manage contact group function shall allow users to add contacts to a group. 
	2.2.1 The system shall allow the user to add contacts to the group.
	2.2.2 The system shall allow the user to add a contact to the group by selecting from the existing contacts.
	2.2.3 The system shall allow the user to add a contact to the group by searching contact name.
	
2.3 The sort contact by group name function shall allow users to sort groups by group name.
	11.1 The system shall set the default sort order by the time the group is added, which means the latest groups list first.
	11.2 The system shall allow the user to sort groups in alphabetical order.


3.Other
3.1 The zoom in function shall allow the user to magnify the view.
3.2 The zoom out function shall allow the user to decrease the view.
3.2 The scroll function shall allow the user to scroll whenever necessary.



